---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — David Henzel"
  description="David Henzel is a serial entrepreneur, recovering introvert, and creator of the Love Not Fear operating system. 20+ years building companies, now focused on helping people find their purpose."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pt-24 pb-16">
    <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-start gap-12">

      <div class="shrink-0">
        <img
          src="/images/david-headshot.png"
          alt="David Henzel"
          class="w-full md:w-72 h-80 object-cover rounded-xl border border-border"
        />
      </div>

      <!-- Name + tagline -->
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-foreground mb-4 leading-tight">
          David Henzel
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          Recovering introvert. Serial entrepreneur. Creator of <a href="https://lovenotfear.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">Love Not Fear</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Bio -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary/60 mb-8">The story</p>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-base text-secondary leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I've always been an entrepreneur. I started my first company as a teenager in Germany, and I've never had a traditional job. What I did have was a problem: I was painfully shy. The kind of shy that made running a meeting with my own team terrifying and a conference call with a customer feel impossible.
        </p>
        <p>
          That started to change when I met Syed Balkhi at WordCamp in Vegas. I was running MaxCDN at the time. After his keynote, Syed grabbed me by the arm and introduced me to every mover and shaker in the WordPress industry. I watched him and thought: <em>This is what I've been missing.</em> So I forced the change — Toastmasters twice a week, networking events twice a week, for years. Exposure therapy. It worked.
        </p>
        <p>
          But the real shift came from my yoga teacher. One day she said five words that rewired everything: <em>"Every decision in life, you make out of love or out of fear."</em> That simple idea became the lens through which I started seeing my business decisions, my relationships, my daily habits — everything.
        </p>
        <p>
          Then my wife was diagnosed with breast cancer. She's fine today — but it forced me to confront my own mortality. I found myself imagining my deathbed self asking: <em>Did I really do what I was supposed to do?</em> I was running a successful company, but I realized: <strong class="text-foreground">the biggest risk isn't failing at something new. The biggest risk is succeeding at something that doesn't matter.</strong>
        </p>
        <p>
          I sold MaxCDN and rebuilt everything around impact. I founded <a href="https://ltvplus.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">LTVplus</a>, built <a href="https://upcoach.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">upcoach</a>, and launched <a href="https://aioperator.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">AI Operator</a>. Today I run a <a href="/companies" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">portfolio of companies</a> with over 500 employees across SaaS, B2B services, AI consulting, and community.
        </p>
        <p>
          But the thing I'm most passionate about is <a href="https://lovenotfear.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">Love Not Fear</a> — the operating system I built around that yoga teacher's insight. It's a four-pillar framework: find your purpose, define your values, craft your vision, build your habits. We use it to help <a href="https://lovenotfear.com/students" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">students</a> figure out what to do with their lives, <a href="https://lovenotfear.com/entrepreneurs" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">entrepreneurs</a> get clear on what actually matters, and <a href="https://lnfpeople.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-accent underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-70 transition-opacity">companies</a> build teams rooted in purpose.
        </p>
        <p>
          Every company I build, every system I design, every decision I make — it comes back to the same question: <em>is this coming from love, or from fear?</em>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Media mentions -->
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 border-t border-border">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-secondary/60 mb-8">Featured in</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-x-10 gap-y-6">
      {[
        { name: 'Forbes', logo: '/logos/media/forbes.png' },
        { name: 'Inc.', logo: '/logos/media/inc.png' },
        { name: 'Fast Company', logo: '/logos/media/fastcompany.png' },
        { name: 'HuffPost', logo: '/logos/media/huffpost.png' },
        { name: 'YEC', logo: '/logos/media/yec.png' },
        { name: 'The Next Web', logo: '/logos/media/tnw.png' },
        { name: 'VentureBeat', logo: '/logos/media/venturebeat.png' },
      ].map((outlet) => (
        <img
          src={outlet.logo}
          alt={outlet.name}
          class="h-6 w-auto object-contain grayscale opacity-40 hover:grayscale-0 hover:opacity-100 transition-all duration-300"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      ))}
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
